description:
Brazil in order to deal with the public health emergency of international importance due to the coronavirus, the following measures may be adopted starting from 7 February 2020, among others:

VI - exceptional and temporary restriction on entering and leaving the country, according to technical and reasoned recommendation by the National Health Surveillance Agency (Anvisa), by highways, ports or airports;

§ 1 The measures provided for in this article can only be determined based on scientific evidence and analyzes of strategic health information and must be limited in time and space to the minimum necessary for the promotion and preservation of public health.

"Art. 1º 
This Ordinance provides for the exceptional and temporary restriction on the entry of foreigners of any nationality into the country, pursuant to the provisions of item VI of the caput of art. 3 of Law no. 13,979, of February 6, 2020, as a result of a technical and reasoned recommendation by the National Health Surveillance Agency -Visa for health reasons related to the risks of contamination and spread of the SARS-CoV-2 coronavirus (covid-19 ).

Art 2.
Foreigners of any nationality are allowed to enter the country for thirty days, by road, by other land means or by water transport.

Art. 3
The restrictions referred to in this Ordinance do not apply to:

I - Brazilian, born or naturalized;

II - immigrant with permanent residence, for a fixed or indefinite period, in Brazilian territory;

III - foreign professional on mission in the service of an international organization, as long as duly identified;

IV - foreign employee accredited to the Brazilian Government;

V - foreigner who is:

a) spouse, partner, son, father or curator of a Brazilian;

b) whose entry is specifically authorized by the Brazilian Government in view of the public interest or for humanitarian reasons; and

c) bearer of the National Migration Registry

VI - cargo transportation.

